### 1) Create account (valid) - should return 201
POST http://localhost:8085/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "12345678",
  "sortCode": "12-34-56",
  "holderName": "Jane Smith",
  "openingBalance": 500.00
}


### 2) Create account (blank holderName) - should return 400
POST http://localhost:8085/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "12345678",
  "sortCode": "12-34-56",
  "holderName": "",
  "openingBalance": 500.00
}


### 3) Create account (bad accountNumber - not 8 digits) - should return 400
POST http://localhost:8085/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "ABC",
  "sortCode": "12-34-56",
  "holderName": "Jane Smith",
  "openingBalance": 500.00
}


### 4) Create account (bad sortCode - wrong format) - should return 400
POST http://localhost:8085/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "12345678",
  "sortCode": "123456",
  "holderName": "Jane Smith",
  "openingBalance": 500.00
}


### 5) Create account (negative balance) - should return 400
POST http://localhost:8085/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "12345678",
  "sortCode": "12-34-56",
  "holderName": "Jane Smith",
  "openingBalance": -50.00
}


### 6) Create account (edge case - zero balance) - should return 201
POST http://localhost:8085/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "87654321",
  "sortCode": "99-88-77",
  "holderName": "John Doe",
  "openingBalance": 0.00
}


### 7) Create account (edge case - multiple errors) - should return 400 with multiple field errors
POST http://localhost:8085/api/accounts
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountNumber": "",
  "sortCode": "bad",
  "holderName": "",
  "openingBalance": -100
}


### 8) List all accounts - should return 200
GET http://localhost:8085/api/accounts
Accept: application/json
